quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  6,11,"Say, “Travel through the land, then see how was the end of the deniers.”"
  6,12,"Say, “To whom belongs all that is in the heavens and earth?” Say, “To Allah.” He has taken it upon Himself to be Merciful. He will surely gather you for the Day of Resurrection about which there is no doubt. Those who have ruined themselves will not believe"
  6,13,"To Him belongs all that rests in the night and in the day, and He is the All-Hearing, the All-Knowing"
  6,14,"Say [O Prophet], “Should I take any guardian other than Allah, the Originator of the heavens and earth, Who feeds but is not fed?” Say, “I have been commanded to be the first to submit [to Allah] and not to be one of those who associate partners with Allah.”"
  6,15,"Say, “If I disobey my Lord, I fear the punishment of a momentous Day.”"
  6,16,Whoever is spared the punishment on that Day is blessed with His mercy. That is the clear triumph
  6,17,"If Allah afflicts you with harm, there is none to remove it except Him; if He grants you good, He is Most Capable of all things"
  6,18,"He is the Vanquisher over His slaves, and He is the All-Wise, the All-Aware"
  6,19,"Say, “Whose testimony is the greatest?” Say, “Allah is Witness between me and you. This Qur’an has been revealed to me so that I may warn you thereby and whomsoever it reaches. Do you really bear witness that there are other gods besides Allah?” Say, “I do not bear such witness.” Say, “Indeed, He is One God, and I disown all that you associate [with Him].”"
  6,20,"Those to whom We gave the Scripture recognize him [Muhammad] just as they recognize their own sons. Those who have ruined their own souls will not believe"